# tui4kas - Cursor Rules

## Project
Terminal UI dashboard for Kaspa L1 blockchain nodes. Rust edition 2024, async with tokio.

## Stack
- **TUI**: ratatui + crossterm
- **RPC**: kaspa-wrpc-client + kaspa-rpc-core (git dep, rev 10116df)
- **Async**: tokio (full features)
- **CLI**: clap (derive)

## Architecture
- Shared state via `Arc<tokio::sync::Mutex<App>>` (defined in `src/app.rs`)
- Background RPC polling in `src/rpc/client.rs` (`RpcManager::start_polling`)
- Event loop in `src/main.rs` reads crossterm events from `src/event.rs`
- UI tabs in `src/ui/` — each tab has its own renderer
- RPC response types wrapped in UI-friendly structs in `src/rpc/types.rs`

## Conventions
- Run `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` before suggesting changes are complete
- Don't use raw kaspa RPC types in UI code — use the wrapper structs from `rpc/types.rs`
- No test suite yet — verify with clippy and manual testing
- Vim-style command line (`:` to open) with history support
